   {:e #blake3 "3919e2a80a6adae4addb80bc10b2bf5813496dea487f1614987741499e825eec" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Paired testing task for S045-Q1 (frontier score normalization), S045-Q2 (latest-wins test), S045-Q3 (cross-type winner test), S045-Q4 (scan merge), S045-Q5 (dead arm cleanup).\n\nUNIT TESTS (4 new tests, property-based where possible):\n\n1. test_assign_to_concepts_latest_wins (DEFECT-004):\n   - Property: In append-only store with two :concept/embedding assertions for same entity, assign_to_concepts uses the later assertion.\n   - Setup: store_with_schema(), add concept with embedding A at tx=10, embedding B at tx=11.\n   - Assert: observation matching B gets higher similarity than observation matching A.\n   - Failure diagnostic: If test fails, log both embeddings, both cosine similarities, and which was used.\n\n2. test_frontier_normalized_scores (DEFECT-001):\n   - Property: After normalization, all candidate scores are in [0.0, 1.0].\n   - Setup: Store with one Explore(score=3), one Deepen(score=0.8), one Bridge(score=10).\n   - Assert: winner.score <= 1.0. All candidates (if exposed) have score in [0,1].\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log raw_score and normalized score for each candidate, showing the normalization math.\n\n3. test_frontier_all_three_candidates (DEFECT-005):\n   - Property: When all three candidate types return results, the winner is the type with highest normalized score.\n   - Setup: Store with 5 :pkg/* entities + edges (Explore), high-variance concept (Deepen), two disjoint-membership concepts (Bridge).\n   - Assert: result is Some, result.kind is deterministic, all three types appear in candidate list.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log full candidate list with kinds, raw scores, and normalized scores.\n\n4. test_frontier_normalization_single_type (edge case):\n   - Property: With only Deepen candidates (no Explore or Bridge), normalization still works and best Deepen wins.\n   - Setup: Store with two high-variance concepts, no pkg entities, no bridge gaps.\n   - Assert: result.kind == Deepen, score == 1.0 for the winner.\n   - Failure diagnostic: Log candidate list showing only Deepen entries.\n\nE2E VERIFICATION:\n- Existing e2e_frontier_steering.sh already covers multi-membership and frontier output. Verify that normalized scores don't break any of the 7 existing E2E checks by running: ./scripts/e2e_frontier_steering.sh\n\nREGRESSION GATE:\n- Run full cargo test (expect 2009 + 4 = 2013 tests passing, 0 failing).\n- Run cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings.\n\nDEPENDS-ON: S045-Q1 (normalization must be implemented before normalized score tests can pass)." :op :assert}
